description: दशामाता की कथा || Dasha Mata Ki Katha || दशा माता व्रत कथा || Dasha mata ki kahaniआज 6 अप्रैल 2021 को #दशामाता के व्रत के अवसर पर मैं आप सभी के समक्ष दशा माता की  प्राचीन एवं पौराणिक कथा दशा माता की कथा प्रस्तुत कर रही हूं। दशा माता का व्रत होली के बाद दशमी दिन किया जाता है इसे होली की दशा भी कहा जाता है। दशा माता घर की बुरी दशा को अच्छी दशा में बदल  देती है और  धनधान्य तथा सुख समृद्धि प्रदान  करती हैं।  आज इस वीडियो में  मैं दशा माता की  पुराणों में वर्णित दशा माता व्रत  कथा लेकर आई हूं। दशा माता की कहानी के अनुसार राजा नल ने दशा माता के डोरे का अपमान किया था और परिणाम स्वरूप राज्य तथा पुत्र सुख सभी से वंचित हो गए थे। फिर उनकी पत्नी रानी दमयंती ने दशा माता का व्रत करके राजसी ठाठ-बाट, पुत्र पुत्र धनधान्य तथा सुख समृद्धि को पुनः प्राप्त किया। हे दशा माता,  जैसे आपने राजा नल और रानी दमयंती को उनका राज्य, मान सम्मान तथा सुख समृद्धि  फिर से प्रदान की, वैसे ही हम सब की दशा को भी हमेशा अच्छा  बनाए रखना। हम सब पर अपनी कृपा करना मां दशा माता। चलिए देखते हैं दशा माता की व्रत की कथा और जोर से बोलते हैं दशा माता की जय | दशा माता की जयHello friends, today on 6th April 2021, on the occasion of fasting of Dasha Mata, I am presenting to you all the ancient and mythological Dasha Mata vrat katha . The Dasha Mata vrat is observed on the tenth day after Holi and people listen #dashamatavratkatha on his day Holi Dasha. Dasha Mata transforms the bad state of the house into a good state and provides prosperity and happiness. Today in this video of Dasha mata ki vrat katha , I have brought the katha mentioned in Puranas of Dasha Mata. According to the Dash mata ki kahani,  King Nal insulted Dasha Mata's thread and as a result the he was deprived of his kingdom. Then his wife Rani Damayanti observed Dasha Mata vrat and regained d happiness and prosperity. O'Dasha Mata, just as you gave Raja Nal and Rani Damayanti their kingdom, honor and happiness and prosperity again, likewise keep the condition of all of us always good. God bless us all, Mother Dasha. let was watch Dasha mata ka vrat ki katha and say loudly #dashamata ki jai

title: Kaalapani 25 Years Special Video | Priyadarshan | Mohanlal | Prabhu | Linto Kurian
tags: [none]
description: 25 Years of KAALAPANI Kaalapani (transl. Cellular Jail) is a 1996 Indian Malayalam-language epic historical drama film co-written and directed by Priyadarshan. Set in 1915, the film focuses on the lives of Indian freedom fighters incarcerated in the Cellular Jail in Andaman and Nicobar Islands during the British Raj. The ensemble cast includes Mohanlal, Prabhu Ganesan, Tabu, Amrish Puri, Nedumudi Venu, Sreenivasan, Tinnu Anand, Annu Kapoor, Alex Draper, Sankaradi, and Vineeth. The film was produced by Mohanlal for Pranavam Arts in association with R. Mohan's Shogun Films.The film is about the lives of prisoners in British India who are brought to Kālā Pānī, the Cellular Jail in Port Blair, Andaman and Nicobar Islands. The name Kalapani is derived from the mode of imprisonment in British India. Ilaiyaraaja composed the music, the cinematography was by Santosh Sivan, and the editing by N. Gopalakrishnan. The film introduced Dolby Stereo into Malayalam cinema. It was made on a budget of ₹6.00 crore, making it the costliest Malayalam film made until then.Kaalapani was released on 6 April 1996 in 450 theaters worldwide, which was the largest release for any Indian film until then. The film is now regarded as one of the classics in Malayalam cinema.[2] Originally made in Malayalam, the film was dubbed and released in Hindi as Saza-E-Kala Pani, Tamil as Siraichalai, and in Telugu as Kaala Pani. Amitabh Bachchan bought the Hindi dubbing rights, besides narrating the prologue for the Hindi version.[3] The film won three National Film Awards, including the awards for Best Art Direction (Sabu Cyril), Best Special Effects (S. T. Venky), and Best Cinematography (Santosh Sivan). Along with that it won six Kerala State Film Awards.Softwares Used : Final Cut Pro X, After EffectsEdited by : Linto KurianThumbnail Design : ALBERT LFAFacebook : https://m.facebook.com/linto.kurian.54Instagram : https://www.instagram.com/linto_kurian/
